<br>
Just had a 2 warr, 1 sk, 1 druid, 1 shammy and me party yesterday. Boy, those melees (if not uber) kill soooo slow ... once we took on two mobs in Pos, two trees. I took one solo with shammy pet (means pretty much solo, lol) and my pet. My mob was down waaaay earlier than theirs ;-) So far regarding mage-power.<br>
<br>
On a sidenote, the group still rocked, cause we didnt do static camping but roamed the whole coastal area in PoS. Was like in the old days. Killed all we saw. Had to watch for adds, still couldnt always prevent them, even had wipes and deaths. But my god this was REAL FUN. Best group I had in ages. In PoP its really nice to have one MT to control mobs a bit better, positioning and such (enrage!).<br>
<br>
So, for every group we do, I would suggest to bring at least one tank (SK for example), one chanter and one cleric. Rest can be mages.<br>
<br>
We did most of the mage epic stuff with a mainly mage-based force. So I can say out of experience: mage-based groups rock; make that pet-class-based groups.<br>
<br>
Regards,<br>
<br>
